"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here. Part of the reason why I am starting a market garden out of my backyard is to see if it's possible. I'm very excited about the idea of a backyard garden providing a lot of my food calories because these food calories, the way I garden, are living calories. This food has a living element to it. The bacteria and the prokaryotes that are on all of our food are kept intact, and that's something that doesn't necessarily happen with conventional farming and distribution, supermarket chains and all of this. So this food is fundamentally healthier for you. It's improving your biomes. It's telling your bacteria how to do a better job. And so my goal here is not only to have a backyard that I can feed off, but also where I can make some money and show an example of maybe how the victory garden concept where Americans start feeding themselves from their backyards becomes a thing. And a great way to jumpstart that is to show that you can actually make some money off of it as well. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here.\",\n      \"start\": 0.24,\n      \"end\": 3.04,\n      \"duration\": 2.8,\n      \"confidence\": 0.989,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.992\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n 